### 1. Check server status
GET {{host}}/api/status

### 2. Simulate Orthanc webhook - store a DICOM instance
###    Note: this will happen automatically if you upload an image via Orthanc's web ui
POST {{host}}/api/orthanc/instances
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "orthancId": "orthanc-test-001",
  "sopInstanceUid": "1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.604688.1234",
  "seriesInstanceUid": "1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.604688.5678",
  "studyInstanceUid": "1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.604688.9999",
  "accessionNumber": "ACC-2026-0001",
  "sopClassUid": "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2",
  "modality": "CR",
  "patientId": "PET-001",
  "patientName": "Buddy"
}

### 3. Create an accession (simulates PIMS integration)
POST {{host}}/api/accessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessionNumber": "7-14538530360-1",
  "studyInstanceUid": "1.2.156.112536.1.2146.116254072099197127.14538530360.1",
  "patientId": "00743-55",
  "patientName": "Roscoe",
  "patientSex": "M",
  "patientDob": "2021-06-17",
  "patientWeight": 12.5,
  "species": "Canine",
  "breed": "Golden Retriever",
  "clientName": "Jane Valesquez",
  "clientId": "CLIENT-042"
}

### 4. Get the worklist (should show the new accession)
GET {{host}}/api/worklist

### 5. Get worklist with filters
GET {{host}}/api/worklist?status=pending&limit=10&offset=0

### 6. Get accession by ID (replace with actual UUID from step 3 response)
GET {{host}}/api/accessions/{{accessionId}}

### 7. Start reading - transition to in_progress
PATCH {{host}}/api/accessions/{{accessionId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

### 8. Complete reading - transition to done
PATCH {{host}}/api/accessions/{{accessionId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "done"
}

### 9. Verify worklist (accession should no longer appear)
GET {{host}}/api/worklist

### 10. Subscribe to worklist SSE events (streams updates in real-time)
GET {{host}}/api/worklist/events
Accept: text/event-stream
